We performed the simulation for a portion of the thin-film sample, which is indicated by a black dashed box in Fig. 5. We assume that the simulated domain is repeated along the horizontal (
                           x
                        ) direction and we apply periodic boundary conditions for the left and right boundaries of the simulation domain. We assume no reaction occurs between the FeCl2 and air, as well as between the Na2S2 and substrate, and employ no-flux boundary conditions for the top and bottom boundaries of the simulation domain.
